## Issues Found

### Non-blocking (warnings)

**W1 — Angular deep-link routing (no 404.html in demo subfolder):**
Direct navigation to `https://michaelwegter.com/demos/solo-law/cms/login` returns a GH Pages 404 (site's 404.html redirects to the React SPA, not the Angular demo). SPA-internal navigation from the demo root works correctly — the EDITOR LOGIN link navigates client-side to the login view without a page load. Impact: low — demo is always accessed via iframe or from root, not deep-linked directly. Users who bookmark a CMS sub-route will land on the portfolio site.

**W2 — WebGPU AI assistant gracefully degraded:**
Headless Playwright has no WebGPU; the AI Content Assistant panel shows "Open any Practice Area or Publication to access the AI Assist panel. In a WebGPU-enabled browse..." — confirmed graceful fallback with no console errors.

**W3 — /solo-law/cms/login route does not exist at API level:**
Correct login endpoint is `/solo-law/auth/login` (POST with `{email, password}` body). The old path `/solo-law/cms/login` returns 404. Demo frontend correctly calls `/auth/login`; no user-facing impact.

### Resolved false positive (test script error)

Initial test run flagged T8 (publications) as a failure because the response is paginated `{items, page, per_page, total}` — not a plain array. API is correct; test logic was wrong. Re-run with corrected assertion: PASS.

## Console Errors on Final Run

None. No console errors, no network 404s on full `networkidle` run from demo root.

## API Direct Verification

```
GET  /solo-law/health          → {"ok":true,"service":"solo-law"}
GET  /solo-law/practice-areas  → 4 items (en), CORS ✓
GET  /solo-law/publications    → {total:5, page:1, per_page:10, items:[...]}
GET  /solo-law/i18n?locale=es  → {locale:"es", overrides:{}}
POST /solo-law/auth/login      → {token:"eyJ...", user:{email,role:"editor"}}
GET  /solo-law/cms/stats       → {practice_areas:4,publications:5,languages:3,brand_assets:0}
```

## handoff
- produced: full Playwright + API verification of live solo-law deployment; all 12 tests pass; 3 non-blocking warnings documented
- decisions: W1 (Angular deep-link 404) is non-blocking — demo accessed via iframe/root only; W2 (WebGPU) is by design with graceful fallback; VERDICT = pass
- next needs: media-capture — record hero flow at demo root, locale switch (EN→ES), and CMS login/dashboard; avoid direct deep-link navigation
- risks: WebGPU AI assist can't be captured in headless screenshot; screenshot will show the "open a PA/publication" placeholder — acceptable for media capture

VERDICT: pass
